  "body": "\r\n\r\n## Issue\r\n\r\nWhen I try to interact with my contract in the test file with await, it can not be fulfilled. \r\nHowever when I changed to use .then() I can run the test successfully.\r\n\r\nI just test an ERC20 token's mint function. \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/42539774/145371180-522473f0-4986-4eb6-9a08-066de42a942c.png)(degis is the contract instance initialized by .deployed())\r\n(ether is my own function and it works well)\r\n\r\n## Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\ntruffle test <my-file> --network dev\r\n\r\n## Expected Behavior\r\n\r\nThe test should pass.\r\n\r\n## Actual Results\r\n\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/42539774/145370374-0bd134d8-cd7a-4005-b478-ce82ef6d9cf7.png)## Environment\r\n\r\n* Operating System:  macOS 11.6\r\n* Ethereum client: ganache-cli (7.0.0-beta1)\r\n* Truffle version (`truffle version`): 5.4.23\r\n* node version (`node --version`): 14.18.1\r\n* npm version (`npm --version`): 8.1.0\r\n",
